description:
Sorry, not sorry, but I do not have the bandwidth to care about ANOTHER government shutdown-themed continuing resolution brouhaha (if I may invoke a little French). It's the same as it ever was, though apparently raising the debt ceiling may or may not be the MAGA position now. Again, while some of you are all "Chip Roy is a uniparty RINO," my brain has already gotten into the egg nog.

However, I can't help but notice that while all the focus is on the incoming president and what he is responsible, we've ALL forgotten that there is a current president. Joe Biden. Remember that guy? CNN's Scott Jennings does. And while his peers in the media are going after Elon Musk for "controlling" Trump, Jennings is wondering about the people who have been controlling (without the finger quotes) Joe Biden for the past four years.

WSJ just
title: Scott Jennings says what we're ALL thinking about the government shutdown: "Hey, what's up with the current president?"
